   "source": [
    "# KIC 9651065"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import exoplanet as xo\n",
    "import pymc3 as pm\n",
    "from maelstrom import Maelstrom\n",
    "from astropy.stats import LombScargle\n",
    "from lightkurve import search_lightcurvefile\n",
    "import lightkurve as lk\n",
    "from maelstrom.orbit import Orbit\n",
    "from exoplanet.orbits import get_true_anomaly\n",
    "import pymc3 as pm\n",
    "import theano.tensor as tt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from matplotlib import rcParams\n",
    "rcParams[\"figure.dpi\"] = 150\n",
    "rcParams[\"savefig.dpi\"] = 300"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "t, y = np.loadtxt('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/danhey/maelstrom/master/paper/lc/9651065_lc.txt', usecols=(0,1)).T"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1800x1050 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ms = Maelstrom(t, y, max_peaks=5, fmin=5, fmax=48)\n",
    "ms.first_look();"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "period_guess = 300\n",
    "a_guess = 200\n",
    "\n",
    "time, flux = ms.time, ms.flux\n",
    "freq = ms.freq\n",
    "weights = ms.get_weights(norm=False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pg = ms.period_search()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "100%|| 300/300 [08:44<00:00,  1.71s/it]\n",
      "100%|| 300/300 [13:08<00:00,  2.55s/it]\n",
      "100%|| 300/300 [08:56<00:00,  1.68s/it]\n",
      "100%|| 300/300 [08:50<00:00,  1.85s/it]\n",
      "100%|| 300/300 [10:05<00:00,  1.83s/it]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "periods = np.linspace(100, 300, 300)\n",
    "results = pg.fit(periods)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ys = np.array([[r[0] for r in row] for row in results])\n",
    "sm = np.sum(ys, axis=0)\n",
    "period_ind = np.argmax(sm)\n",
    "plt.plot(periods[:-2], sm[:-2]);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 19,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from maelstrom.utils import unique_colors\n",
    "\n",
    "hh = unique_colors(len(ms.freq), cmap='Blues')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 28,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1000x618.034 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=mnras_size(240.))\n",
    "\n",
    "ys = np.array([[np.exp(r[1][\"logasini\"]) for r in row] for row in results])\n",
    "for i, c in zip(ys, hh):\n",
    "    plt.plot(periods, i, alpha=1, linewidth=0.8, c=c);\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Period (d)')\n",
    "plt.ylabel(r'a$\\sin{i}$ (s)')\n",
    "plt.ylim(0, None)\n",
    "plt.xlim(100,300)\n",
    "plt.axhline(184., c='r', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=0.7)\n",
    "plt.axvline(272., c='r', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=0.7)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.savefig(overleaf_path + '9651065_period_search.pdf', dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight', pad_inches=0)"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "import theano.tensor as tt\n",
    "from maelstrom.orbit import Orbit\n",
    "\n",
    "with pm.Model() as subdivide_model:\n",
    "    logP = pm.Normal(\"logP\", mu=np.log(272), sd=1.0, testval=np.log(272))\n",
    "    period = pm.Deterministic(\"period\", pm.math.exp(logP))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # The time of conjunction\n",
    "    phi = xo.distributions.Angle(\"phi\", testval=0.5691498)\n",
    "    logs_lc = pm.Normal('logs_lc', mu=np.log(np.std(flux)), sd=10, testval=0.)\n",
    "    logasini = pm.Normal('logasini', mu=np.log(184), sd=10, testval=np.log(184))\n",
    "    asini = pm.Normal(\"asini\", mu=184, sd=10, testval=184)\n",
    "    drift = pm.Normal('drift', mu=0., sd=0.1, testval=0)\n",
    "    # Periastron sampled from uniform angle\n",
    "    omega = xo.distributions.Angle(\"omega\", testval=-0.94)\n",
    "    # Eccentricity\n",
    "    eccen = pm.Uniform(\"eccen\", lower=0, upper=0.9, testval=0.45)\n",
    "    # The baseline flux\n",
    "    mean = pm.Normal(\"mean\", mu=0.0, sd=10.0, testval=0.003)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Here, we generate an Orbit instance and pass in our priors. \n",
    "    orbit = Orbit(period=period, \n",
    "                  lighttime=asini, \n",
    "                  omega=omega, \n",
    "                  eccen=eccen, \n",
    "                  phi=phi, \n",
    "                  freq=0)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # psi is defined to be negative but the light curve model takes 2*pi*f * (time - tau), so \n",
    "    # we must flip tau here to phase it on the same values\n",
    "    td = -1*tt.squeeze(orbit.get_time_delay(td_time) * 86400) # Convert to s\n",
    "    td += drift * td_time\n",
    "    taumodel = pm.Deterministic('taumodel', td - tt.mean(td))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    pm.Normal('obs', mu=taumodel, sd=tt.exp(logs_lc), observed=td_td)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    plt.plot(td_time, xo.eval_in_model(taumodel))\n",
    "    plt.plot(td_time, td_td)"
   ]
  },
